title: Kimberly Lactaoen, MS
text:
I am a bioinformatician with a background in evolutionary biology and biomedical research. I currently work in the Weissman Lab at the Palliative and Advanced Illness Research Center (PAIR Center) at the University of Pennsylvania. I currently contribute to projects involving the use of electronic health records for understanding asthma in adults.
I have earned a Bachelor of Science in Biology and a Master of Science in Developmental and Reproductive Biology from the University of Hawai’i at Mānoa.
I am planning to apply to a PhD program in biomedical informatics (or a related field) this Fall 2025. If you’re going through the same process or have any advice to share, I’d like to connect!
